---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  description="Building mesh backup communications for KC. One person, one router at a time. Want to help?"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50 md:text-5xl">
      I'm building a mesh network for Kansas City.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      Not because I'm some RF expert. I'm just someone who figured out that a $35 radio on my roof can reach 5 miles, and four of these things in the right spots could cover most of the metro with backup communications.
    </p>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      So I put one up. It works. Now I'm looking for help with the other three.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Coordination Banner -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-sunset-amber/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-sunset-amber/5 to-prairie-gold/5 p-6 dark:border-sunset-amber/20 dark:from-sunset-amber/10 sm:p-8">
    <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">
      If you run kansascitymesh.net, I especially want to talk.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      I noticed your domain but couldn't find contact info. This isn't about competing—I just want to build mesh infrastructure in KC, and I'd rather do it together. <a href="/about/coordination" class="text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">Here's why coordination matters.</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Current Status -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Where things stand right now</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-mesh-green">Operational</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Router 1</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          East side. Solar-powered. Covers ~5 mile radius. <strong>Indoors</strong> on top floor next to outward-facing wall. Acting as MQTT gateway for internet connectivity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sunset-amber">Obvious Gap</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Router 2</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <strong>West side is wide open.</strong> If someone with elevation west of State Line deployed a router, they'd bridge the east-west gap. That's the logical next piece.
        </p>
        <a href="/guides/west-side" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
          What Router 2 would look like →
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-ink-500 dark:text-cream-200">Planned</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Routers 3 & 4</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          North and south metro coverage. Once Router 2 is up, these complete the cardinal backbone. Then it's just filling in density.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What This Actually Is -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-blue/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue/5 to-kc-sky/10 p-6 dark:border-kc-sky/20 dark:from-kc-blue/10 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">What this actually is</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>Honestly? It's just fun.</strong> Building infrastructure with cheap radios is cool. Watching messages hop across the city on hardware I deployed is satisfying. Learning RF propagation by actually doing it beats reading forums. That's why I'm doing this.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>But it's also useful.</strong> Backup text messaging that works when cell towers don't. Emergency communications for severe weather, power outages, whatever. Some people care deeply about that. If that's your motivation, great—you'll benefit from this work.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Entry cost: $30-50 for a basic node.</strong> No license needed (915 MHz ISM band). No monthly fees. You own the hardware, the network exists because people participate.
      </p>
      <p>
        This isn't some company or formal organization. It's just infrastructure that I'm building and documenting so others can join. If enough people scatter nodes across KC, we end up with mesh coverage the whole metro can use—for fun, for emergency, for whatever.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How You Can Participate -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Ways to participate</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Get a node</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          $30-50. Pair it with your phone. Join the network. Even indoor nodes add coverage. Start here if you're new to this.
        </p>
        <a href="/get-started/join" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
          How to join →
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Deploy your own router</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Got elevation? Repeater tower, tall house, rooftop access? A solar-powered router is ~$150 and covers miles. West side would make the most impact.
        </p>
        <a href="/guides/repeater-owners" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
          Infrastructure guides →
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Spread the word</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Know ham operators? Emergency comms groups? HOA neighbors who want backup capability? Tell them this exists. Mesh works better with more participants.
        </p>
        <a href="/community/contribute" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
          Other ways to help →
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Not Sure? Start Here -->
  <section class="mt-12 text-center">
    <div class="inline-block rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue to-kc-red p-8 text-cream-50 shadow-card md:p-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Not sure where to start?</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-base opacity-95">
        Read about why I'm using Meshtastic, what it actually does, and whether it's worth your time.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/about/why-meshtastic"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cream-50 px-8 py-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue transition hover:bg-surface-200"
      >
        What is this thing? →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
